    About Hotel Pembridge Palace

    Located in the Bayswater area of London, the Hotel Pembridge Palace Hotel offers modest accommodations in a Victorian property. The hotel is conveniently positioned near Bayswater underground station. Guestrooms feature a direct dial telephone, TV and hairdryer. Internet access is available for a surcharge, while an iron and ironing board can be requested. The hotel features a 24-hour reception and breakfast room. Guests can relax in the hotel courtyard. A continental breakfast is served every morning. Guests will find a host of nearby dining options, with Westbourne Grove featuring a range of restaurants. Alternatively, the West End’s many eateries are just a few stops away on the underground. The Hotel Pembridge Palace Hotel is a five-minute walk from Kensington Gardens and Hyde Park. Guests will find the likes of the Royal Albert Hall and Kensington Palace located nearby. The London Underground offers quick passage to the city’s other famed attractions.

    About Apex Temple Court Hotel

    Just off bustling Fleet Street, Apex Temple Court Hotel is a short two-minute walk from Inner Temple and Middle Temple - both historic Inns of Court. This four-star hotel boasts impressive contemporary interior design that’s complemented by creative fixtures and natural light. The hotel has 204 rooms and suites, an elegant restaurant, wine bar, courtyard, private dining rooms and gym. In each room you’ll find Elemis toiletries, safe, 40” LCD TV with Sky TV, Nespresso coffee machine, Bluetooth speaker and a fridge to store your essentials. You can also make use of complimentary Wi-Fi. Chambers Restaurant serves delicious food throughout the day with a variety of options to choose from. The hotel also has its own bar and lounge that features a tranquilising fireplace – the perfect place to relax. The newly built Amicable Society of Lazy Ballerinas Wine Bar and Private Dining Rooms offer an exciting selection of unique, atmospheric and exclusive spaces to meet, unwind and imbibe.

    About Sofitel London St James

    The 5 star Sofitel St James is located in heart of the city's West End close to many of London’s attractions and in walking distance to many theatres. The hotel is a historic building which, when it was refurbished, maintained and preserved many of the original features. There are 183 guest rooms made up of classic, superior, luxury, Sofitel suite and Prestige Suite. All are en-suite and come with air-conditioning, TV, safe deposit box, internet access and mini bar as standard. The restaurant the Balcon offers fine dining of French cuisine specially prepared by the chef. Afternoon tea is served in the Rose Lounge, the St James’s Bar is now decorated inspired by Coco Chanel's apartment in Paris in the 1920's. 12 meeting rooms all with their own entrance can accommodate up to 180 guests. All rooms are equipped with the latest technology and staff are on hand to ensure everything runs smoothly. The leisure suite features a fully equipped gym and aromatic steam rooms, also a range of beauty treatments and massages are available. Sofitel London St James is a smoke-free property.

    About Travelodge London City Airport

    Travelodge London City Airport offers affordable accommodations and is less than a quarter of a mile from the airport. Rooms offer guests a king-sized Travelodge Dreamer Bed, shower, toiletries, and coffee and tea making facilities. Wi-Fi internet is free for the first 30 minutes per day. Travelodge London City Airport has a car park operated by a third party service. Guests can park their vehicle up to 5 nights for a fee. There is an ATM machine on the property and the hotel offers early check-in and late check-out services. The Bar Café offers a full breakfast buffet as well as evening service with comforting dishes like fish and chips, burgers and pizza. Wines, lagers and more can be ordered from the bar. Galleons Reach Shopping Park is a family-friendly retail centre a mile from the hotel. Canary Wharf and the National Maritime Museum are within a 5-mile radius.

    About Apartment Presidential Kensington

    Presidential Apartments Kensington offers serviced studio and one-bedroom apartments for short and extended stays. The apartments are close to charming gardens and quaint neighbourhoods with easy access to London’s city centre. Apartments feature fully equipped kitchens, washer and dryer, and private bathroom with complimentary toiletries. Free Wi-Fi internet, air conditioning, satellite TV, and safety box are provided for guest convenience. Presidential Apartments Kensington provides cleaning services every weekday, with linen and towel changes twice a week. Upon arrival, guests receive a welcome pack with tea and coffee as well as fresh biscuits. The concierge can book restaurant reservations for guests in the local area, or arrange to have food delivered to the apartment doorstep. The apartments are located in Central London’s most loved districts. The hotel is a short 3-minute walk from Earl’s Court station and exhibition centre and just 5 minutes from Westfield.

    About Chelsea Cloisters

    Located in one of London’s most fashionable suburbs, Chelsea, and by Kensington, the Chelsea Cloisters are serviced apartments for short-term stays. There are 250 apartments set up as studio, one bedroom or two bedroom with weekly rates, sleeping up to five people. Rooms come with a double bed, ironing facilities, en-suite bathroom, TV, table and chairs and basic kitchen appliances and cooking utensils. Rooms have a daily maid service and chargeable Wi-Fi. The site has 24 hour concierge and security with check-in desk and porterage. There are safe deposits in the office, secure parking and multilingual staff. With two restaurants to choose from, guests can opt for Japanese with Sushi des Artistes or opt for Argentinean steak with chain restaurant Gaucho. Galante is an Argentin cocktail bar while Barts styles itself as a speakeasy. The accommodation is by Kensington Palace, Hyde Park and the Science Museum as well as loads of high street shops.

    About Holiday Inn Express London-Royal Docks, Docklands

    Holiday Inn Express London-Royal Docks, Docklands is well placed for access to Canary Wharf and the O2 Arena which are, respectively, approximately three and four miles away. This smart hotel offers a number of room features that are designed to create a home away from home feeling. The 136 rooms feature free Wi-Fi, a flat-screen satellite TV, telephone, and air conditioning. Family rooms are available. A hairdryer is supplied for use in the private bathroom. There is a business centre at Holiday Inn Express London-Royal Docks, Docklands and the property is non-smoking. Parking is available and there is 24-hour reception desk cover. Cooked or continental breakfast choices make for a great start to the day. Later, a restaurant delivery service is offered and the lobby bar serves a range of wines and other drinks. Italian dining is less than 100 yards away at Pepenero Restaurant. Canning Town Underground Station is less than half a mile away, as is a bracing dip in London Royal Docks' open water swimming basin.
